v0.5    - changes to button layout throughout GUI
        - changed code to use SDI_compiler.h so that Connect 4 can
          now be compiled using any compiler, not just vbcc
        - fixed a small problem where Connect 4 would try to use the
          game icon when in an iconified state, even if no such icon
          was found
        - improved speed of graphics remapping
        - better looking gameboard graphic
        - improved speed when clearing pieces for a new game on chunky
          displays (P96 and CGFX)
        - computer player at level 2 is now more careful than before
        - safer loading of preferences file
        - reduced code size for address book handling

v0.4    - added a better computer player
        - added the source for the windows, which was accidentally
          missing from the previous release

v0.3    - finally got around to calling it version 0.3!
        - cleaned up GUI layout in the main window
        - increased the number of pens allowed in the pieces graphics
        - changed the Player Address Book to accommodate computer and
          network players more clearly
        - changed preferences file format to reflect PAB changes
        - when a game was complete (won or drawn) the LED on the main
          board wasn't lit for the last person to place a piece in the
          gameboard: fixed
        - added a computer player
        - changed $VER string so that version number appears
          without having to use the "full" switch with the
          version command
        - name fields no longer left blank: will automatically
          substitute in the name(s) "Player 1" and "Player 2"
          instead
        - Changed the winner's window to indicate which colour
          counters the winner was using, as well as their name

v0.2    - why isn't this version 0.3? No idea...
        - stability improvements
        - fixed MUIM_Setup/MUIM_Cleanup colour remapping bug
        - loads from Workbench
        - iconifies using own icon
        - About window changed, plus other minor GUI changes
        - graphics file sizes reduced
        - removed "mask" and "blank_square" files: data now
          incorporated into executable

v0.2    - erm... plays Connect 4 now! ;)

v0.1    - internal, first version. Loads a picture of a Connect 4
          board, but that's as good as it gets at the moment!


